Senate Spending Chairman Says Deeper Defense Cut ‘Detrimental’

-- B y   R o x a n a   T i r o n
-- 
2011-09-15T18:34:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/senate-spending-chairman-says-deeper-defense-cut-detrimental-.html
The chairman of the Senate
Appropriations Committee said cutting the  defense budget  more
than already planned would be “detrimental” to national
security.  Senator Daniel Inouye, a Hawaii Democrat, said his panel
had cuts of $26 billion in its $513 billion defense spending
bill.  To contact the reporter on this story:
